This paper deals with device-free localization using wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new model for spatial impact area, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, indicating a possible fit for information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also describes a real-time imaging system, which involves control and system theory, indicating a possible fit for systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the experiments involve data processing and analysis, indicating a possible fit for multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
